      <text>7.1.9 (Line tangent to parabola)</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>The line with equation \(y= {@l@}\) is tangent to the parabola \( y = {@p@} \). Find the value of \(k.\)</p><p>\(k = \) [[input:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]] [[validation:ans1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>The line&nbsp;\(y= {@l@}\) is tangent to the parabola \( y = {@p@} \) when these two intersect at one point.&nbsp;</p><p>So we solve \[ \begin{align*} {@l@} &amp;= {@p@} \\ {@p-l@} &amp;= 0 \end{align*}\]</p><p>To intersect at one point means that the&nbsp;discriminant of this quadratic equation should be \(0\).</p><p>We have \(a={@a@}\),&nbsp;\(b={@b-m@}\) and \(c={@c-k@}\), so</p><p>\[ \begin{align*} b^2-4ac = {@(b-m)^2@} - 4({@a@})({@c-k@}) &amp;= 0&nbsp; \\ {@expand((b-m)^2- 4*a*(c-k))@} &amp;= 0&nbsp; \\ k &amp;= {@ta1@}\end{align*} \]</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
